      "question": "What does \"heirloom\" mean in Ethiopian coffee?",
      "answer": "\"Heirloom\" is a trade term for the thousands of indigenous Arabica varieties native to Ethiopia's forests. Unlike standardized cultivars (SL28, Caturra) bred in other countries, these landraces evolved naturally over centuries, producing extraordinary genetic diversity and unique flavor potential in each region."
